      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>In ''The Pursuit of Autonomy,'' Alan Wolfe offers a current example of lib-eral propaganda. ''Conservatives,'' he writes, ''detest government.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>In ''The Pursuit of Autonomy,'' Alan Wolfe offers a current example of lib-eral propaganda. ''Conservatives,'' he writes, ''detest government.''</p>
        <p>It is, perhaps, rather more accurate to perceive among liberals a loathing for limited government. And as limited government was the intention of the founders of our republic, I should think liberals have more of an argument with, say, Madison, than with those of us they would regard as mean-spirited extremists.</p>
        <p>David R. Zukerman</p>
        <p>Bronx</p>
      </block>
